                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d679">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.51/51: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-18T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 18, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>761. Your 1233, July 14, 5 p.m. You are requested to inform the Chargé at Jidda
                    that the Department instructs him to approach the Saudi Arabian Government in
                    accordance with your recommendations.</p>
                <p>War Department is being informed of your telegram under reference, and of the
                    present instructions.</p>
                <p>Casoc estimates the value of British assistance to Saudi Arabia this year at
                    nearly 4 million pounds sterling and states that the Company is furnishing 3
                    million dollars at the rate of 500,000 every 2 months.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
